pr_body:
# Vue.js Activity Template #
This is an Activity Template to create activities in Vue.js. Currently it is an activity named 'ActivityTemplateVue' and runs the basic Pawn activity for testing purposes.

## Structure ##
I have decomposed the major functionalities into importable components which can be found under `/js/components`.

Steps to use any component (Adding the toolbar for example):
1. Import the component using `<script>` tag in `index.html`
```html
  ...
  <script src="js/components/SugarToolbar.js"></script>    //Import the toolbar component
  <script src="js/activity.js"></script>              //Make sure you import activity.js in the end
</body>
```
2. Create and use the component instance in `index.html` (Don't forget the `ref` attribute)
```html
<div id="app">
  <sugar-toolbar ref="SugarToolbar">
    <sugar-toolitem id="add-button" v-on:click="onAddClick" v-bind:title="l10n.stringAddPawn"></sugar-toolitem>
  </sugar-toolbar>
  ...
```

## Benefits ##
* Easy to integrate a specific functionality.
* Decomposed and encapsulated code making it easier to manage. 
* More flexibility in project design.
* Adds a layer of abstraction. New contributors can focus on activity-specific code rather than the working of Sugarizer functionalities.

## Can be improved ##
* Palette workflow
* ~Localization workflow~

This is an initial template structure and is open to changes. All suggestions are welcome.

pr_body:
This is an initial build of Fraction Bounce game for issue #205 implementing the single player mode. Adding this to get an initial review on the progress made so far.

![fractionBounce1](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/40134655/76235558-43f19400-6251-11ea-875e-c14fdead9a07.gif)

Single player mode is completely playable through keyboard with working options such as changing ball & background images, percentage mode, etc. The smileys are logged similar to the python activity. Custom fractions can also be added and will be saved in the journal.

**Yet to implement:**
- [x] ~~Sectors mode for the ball~~
- [x] ~~Toolbar help text~~
- [x] ~~Adding custom ball/background from journal~~
- [x] ~~Add Touch Controls~~
- [x] ~~Tutorial for the activity~~

This is an initial build hence it might contain some bugs. Please review the progress @llaske and @ashish0910 and let me know the changes if any.

pr_title: Replaced Uglify-js by Terser for ES6+ minification
pr_body:
This PR replaces the Uglify-js dependency by new and improved Terser, which can minify ES6+ syntax as well. The modification was discussed [here](https://github.com/llaske/sugarizer-apkbuilder/issues/3#issuecomment-612850952). 

The performance benchmarks for Terser can be seen [here](https://github.com/babel/minify#benchmarks).

Please check llaske/sugarizer#783 for configuration details.

pr_title: [Feature for #3] Added Activity choice through command-line
pr_body:
Implemented and tested my solution as discussed in #3.

***Testing***
To test the changes, edit the `make_android.sh` as per this PR by changing the --entrypoint for docker. Then execute the following command:
```shell
bash make_android.sh exclude-activities=TurtleBlocksJS,Abecedarium,Scratch
```
Note: Specify the activity name as the string before `.activity` for its directory in `/activities` separated by commas without spaces. Eg: "EbookReader" for EbookReader.activity

Yet to implement:
- [ ] Possibly specifying the choices through environment variables

pr_title: [Issue #235 fix] Fixed scroll on reordering activities
pr_body:
Fixes #235 
Removed the jquery-sortable dependency and handling the sorting and drag-and-drops using the already existing jquery-ui dependency. Calling the updateActivities() function only when the list has been updated reducing the unnecessary server calls. Also added a smooth animation while reordering.

![dragScrollFix](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/40134655/75980978-880b2e80-5f09-11ea-8d88-13fd5c63c84e.gif)
